<subSubSection lastPageId="72" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="71.[199,1436,1962,2024]" box="[199,1436,1997,2024]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1997,2023]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the group of dark coloured 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1103,1998,2024]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis box="[942,1015,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Druon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1118,1259,1998,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[1118,1259,1998,2024]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">D. alexandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1273,1389,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gregori">
<emphasis box="[1273,1389,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">D. gregori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Lyon" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[151,331,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flocculentum">
<emphasis box="[151,331,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D. flocculentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[386,503,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gregori">
<emphasis box="[386,503,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D. gregori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the OOL is as long as diameter of lateral ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1154,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–49" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1758,1782]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,934,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-309@23.[173,1414,921,1734]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 46–49. Druon gregori, sp. nov., asexual female. 46–48, head: 46, frontal view, 47, dorsal view, 48, posterior view. 49, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520498/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
) while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1269,1395,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serretae">
<emphasis box="[1269,1395,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D. serretae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the OOL is 1.5× as long as diameter of lateral ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[720,819,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 222–227" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1855,1879]" captionTargetBox="[153,1428,672,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-141@71.[153,1435,669,1832]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 222–227. Druon serretae, sp. nov., asexual female. 222–225, head: 222, frontal view, 223, dorsal view, part, 224, lateral view, 225, posterior view. 226, antenna. 227, mesosoma and propleura, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520637/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 223</figureCitation>
). It closely resembles to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[1095,1236,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[1095,1236,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D. alexandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Lyon" baseAuthorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flocculentum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D. flocculentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the shape of the head (see the key) and the notaulus is complete (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1192,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–231" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[159,1419,431,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-152@72.[154,1434,417,1789]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 228–231. Druon serretae, sp. nov., asexual female. 228, mesosoma, lateral view. 229–230, mesoscutum and mesoscutellum dorsal view. 231, metascutellum and propodeum, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520641" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520641/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 229</figureCitation>
), while incomplete in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,292,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandri">
<emphasis box="[151,292,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D. alexandri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuesta-Porta &amp; Melika &amp; Nicholls &amp; Stone &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Lyon" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[347,526,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Druon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flocculentum">
<emphasis box="[347,526,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">D. flocculentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[541,621,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[211,1380,747,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-303@11.[199,1389,741,1812]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. Druon alexandri, sp. nov., asexual female. 6, mesosoma, lateral view. 7, mesoscutum, dorsal view. 8, mesoscutellum, dorsal view. 9, metascutellum and propodeum, posterodorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520475/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
, 
